></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-02/260226-trump-white-house-ballroom-vl-458p-cdb73a.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Jon Elswick</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Artist renderings and diagrams of the new White House East Wing and Ballroomoom</media:text><media:description type="plain">An excavator sits on the rubble after the East Wing of the White House was demolished in October 2025, before construction of a new ballroom. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260426-white-house-ballroom-ww-830-572af3.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 17:29:07 GMT</pubDate><title>Republicans propose $1 billion in taxpayer dollars to secure Trump ballroom</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 17:36:37 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 13:18:53 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Blake Lively attended the Met Gala on Monday after reaching a settlement with former co-star and director Justin Baldoni, bringing an abrupt end to their year-long legal battle. Lively sued Baldoni and his production company for waging what she called a smear campaign against her after she accused him of sexual harassment on the set of their 2024 film “It Ends With Us,” which Baldoni consistently denied. NBC’s Laura Jarrett reports for TODAY.</description><expires>2056-05-05T12:31:58.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/it-ends-with-a-deal-justin-baldoni-and-blake-lively-settle-lawsuit-262752837843</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni Settle ‘It Ends With Us’ Legal Battle</media:title><media:player url="https://www.today.com/video/it-ends-with-a-deal-justin-baldoni-and-blake-lively-settle-lawsuit-262752837843"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505_S3_1920x1080-te6gza.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">Blake Lively attended the Met Gala on Monday after reaching a settlement with former co-star and director Justin Baldoni, bringing an abrupt end to their year-long legal battle. Lively sued Baldoni and his production company for waging what she called a smear campaign against her after she accused him of sexual harassment on the set of their 2024 film “It Ends With Us,” which Baldoni consistently denied. NBC’s Laura Jarrett reports for TODAY.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505_S3_1920x1080-te6gza.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 12:31:52 GMT</pubDate><title>Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni Settle ‘It Ends With Us’ Legal Battle</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 13:18:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 13:36:36 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Nearly 150 passengers, including 17 Americans, are trapped on a cruise ship off the coast of West Africa after seven possib